@startuml feedback-plataform-container
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Container.puml

title Container Diagram - Feedback Platform
caption Illustrates the main containers of the Feedback Platform and their interactions.

System_Boundary(plataforma_feedback, "Feedback Platform") {

    Container(web_app, "Web Application", "SPA", "Provides the user interface for the feedback platform.", $link="../components/web-app-component.svg")
    Container(api, "API", "NestJS (Node.js)", "RESTful API that exposes business functionalities and manages data.", $link="../components/api-component.svg")
    ContainerDb(database, "Database", "PostgreSQL", "Stores all platform data (users, feedback, settings).")
    ContainerDb(cache_redis, "Data Cache", "Redis", "Caches data to optimize performance.")
}

Person(colaborador, "Collaborator", "Offers and receives feedback.")
Person(lider, "Leader", "Offers, receives, and manages feedback from direct reports.")
Person(administrador, "Administrator", "Manages the platform, users, and settings.")

System_Ext(servico_email, "Email Service", "Email sending service for notifications.")

colaborador -down-> web_app : Uses (HTTP/HTTPS)
lider -down-> web_app : Uses (HTTP/HTTPS)
administrador -down-> web_app : Manages via (HTTP/HTTPS)

web_app -down-> api : Consumes API (JSON/HTTPS)

api -down-> database : Reads and Writes data (SQL)
api -down-> cache_redis : Reads and Writes cached data
api -down-> servico_email : Sends emails (SMTP/API)

right header [[../contexts/feedback-plataform-context.svg back to context]] 

@enduml